RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DINOS DIXIE was sent leaving the start and showed speed while dictating terms in the early going, drew to a clear lead while well handled along the turn, was kept to task while in hand to mid-stretch and pulled away in the final sixteenth while under mild late urging. JAIME'S COMMITMENT lacked early speed while a bit green in the early stages, saved ground along the turn, closed well in the stretch run, could not impact the winner in deep stretch but continued his late gain and was up in the final strides to secure the place. WEE BEASTIE chased the decent pace from the inside, tipped two wide for the drive and made a mild gain at the furlong marker, could not keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and was outfinished for the place in the final strides, while holding clearly in the end for the show. BOBBED N LURED broke in the air and was off slowly, chased outside of rivals into the turn, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch and did not threaten. NICKEY BIRD was prominent in the early stages and stalked the decent pace into the turn, lost position while two wide along the bend, was coaxed along three wide into the drive, was outrun to mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Dinos Dixie
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,showed speed,well handled,kept to task stretch,held sway

ENTRY.NAME: Jaime's Commitment
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow,green,inside,closed well stretch,up for 2nd

ENTRY.OWNER: Fishbough William L and Fishbough-Miller Alyxandria

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbed N Lured
ENTRY.OWNER: Daehling Farms LLC and Stortz Marcia

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Farias Adan Newman Robert Schadick David and Sylvia Earle

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DICK BEST was sent to establish a forward position in the early running, pressed the solid pace into the turn then dueled with LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH along the bend while setting solid fractions to the quarter marker, continued to duel with LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH into the drive, took a narrow lead into the final sixteenth and edged away in deep stretch to prevail. LUCK'S ROYAL FLUSH was hustled to establish the early lead, set a pressured pace into the turn, dueled along the bend with DICK BEST while carving solid fractions, continued that battle into the lane, grudgingly gave way in the final furlong and just held for the place. MIGHTY MATT stalked the solid early pace, gained ground while two wide along the turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong pole, was outfinished in deep stretch and just missed for the place, while clear of the rest for the show. SASQUATCH RIDE was allowed to settle, raced two wide into the turn, mounted a four wide bid into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker and could not muster a final response. FULLY LOADED chased the solid early pace from the inside, lost position on the turn and tired in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Dick Best
ENTRY.OWNER: Blaine D Wright Racing Stable LLC and Serena August

ENTRY.NAME: Sasquatch Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,2wide turn,bid 4wide into stretch,evenly,no final kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAREEHA (IRE) assumed command at the start and dictated terms into the first turn, set moderate fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, drew to a clear lead along the far turn, was given a reminder tap in upper stretch and drew off approaching the furlong pole, was kept to task to the final sixteenth and was geared down in the late stages as much the best at the finish. TIZ MY PRINCESS was crowded at the start and was away a bit slowly, settled along the rail into the first turn then was coaxed along two wide into the backstretch run, improved position heading to the half-mile marker, gave chase while two wide along the far turn, was no match for the winner in the stretch drive but stayed on to best the rest and galloped out nicely past the wire. PRESTIGIOUS settled in mid-pack while saving ground in the early running, saved all of the ground to the far turn, could not impact the top two in the stretch run but stayed on in the final stages and outfinished SOUTHERN BLESSING to secure the show. SOUTHERN BLESSING broke in a bit at the start and crowded TIZ MY PRINCESS leaving the break, was prominent into the first turn and attended to the moderate pace into the backstretch run, lost ground heading to the far turn, could not keep pace with SAREEHA in upper stretch, gave way in the final stages and was outfinished for the show. JACQUELINE COCHRAN settled three wide into the first turn, travelled inside of an outer rival through the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the far turn and did not offer a late response in the stretch. VALENTINE CRASHER paused at the start and was off a bit slowly, was unhurried in the early stages and settled outside of rivals into the first turn, raced outside of a rival through the backstretch run and came three wide into the far turn, slipped to the rail in upper stretch and did not threaten in the drive. I'M GONNA SHINE crowded a neighboring rival at the start, was forwardly placed into the first turn and stalked the moderate pace while three wide into the backstretch run, lost position along the far turn, chased to mid-stretch and tired in the final stages. FRESNO CHILE was crowded leaving the start by a neighboring rival and was off a bit slowly, recovered to stalk the early pace while widest into the first turn, maintained a four wide trip through the backstretch run while chasing the pacesetter, continued to race widest while into the far turn, lost position into the drive and came up empty in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Southern Blessing
ENTRY.OWNER: Berger Jeffrey and Valenzuela Thomas N

ENTRY.NAME: Valentine Crasher
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow,settled,4wide early,3wide 2nd turn,no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Prestigious
ENTRY.OWNER: Opas Lawrence and Sinatra Frank R

ENTRY.NAME: Fresno Chile
ENTRY.COMMENT: crowded start,stalked outside,4wide both turns,empty stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LISA'S VALENTINE broke alertly and showed good early speed leaving the start, contested the decent pace into the turn, dueled with MALASADA along the bend while inside of that rival, was confronted by VALERIE in upper stretch and held a narrow lead over that rival to the furlong marker, shook free into deep stretch and drew clear in the final stages in a good debut. VALERIE was forwardly placed in the early running and stalked the decent pace while outside of rivals, maintained a three wide path to the quarter marker, was roused into the lane and confronted LISA'S VALENTINE in upper stretch, battled with that foe to the furlong marker, could not match strides heading to the final sixteenth and just held for the place at the finish. PLEASANT WARNING chased the decent early pace from mid-pack, ran in pursuit while two wide along the turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, raced evenly to the furlong marker, lacked a final response in deep stretch but ran on and just missed for the place, while just holding for the show. BLAZIN BAE away slowly from the gate, chased outside of rivals in the early going, came three wide to the quarter marker and was asked for run four wide into the stretch, made a mild gain at the furlong marker, was gaining in deep stretch and just missed for the minor awards. ALL HALLOWS was bumped by an outer rival at the start and was off slowly, lacked early speed and trailed into the turn, improved position while two wide along the bend then was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, gained ground at the furlong marker and improved position in the final sixteenth. HAUGHTY KITTY chased from towards the rear in the early running, was steered two wide into the turn and dropped back along the bend, raced three wide into the stretch drive, was able to offer a mild late rally but did not threaten. ROUSING STAR chased the decent early pace from the inside, lost ground on the turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker and gave way in the late stages. MOHAYHAYTHEBOLD chased the decent pace from the inside and weakened in the stretch. MALASADA was prominent in the early running and disputed the decent pace with LISA'S VALENTINE, raced on even terms with that rival into the turn, pressed the pace while between rivals nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the drive and faded in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: All Hallows
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start,2wide turn,3wide stretch,came on late

ENTRY.NAME: Haughty Kitty
ENTRY.OWNER: Conner Dennis Jacobsen Wade and McKeen Michael

ENTRY.NAME: Rousing Star
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,lost ground turn,evenly to 1/8,gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Blazin Bae
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly,chased outside,4wide into stretch,gaining late

ENTRY.NAME: Lisa's Valentine
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,contested pace,shook free,drew clear,good debut

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 5 5F Turf CR: 90. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STRETCH RUN was prominent in the early running and disputed the pace with DAD BOD into the turn, shook free along the bend and led into upper stretch, bumped and made contact with REFI NOW at the three-sixteenths marker, held a safe lead to the furlong pole, kept to task under steady late urging and prevailed in a drive at the finish. REFI NOW settled off of the early pace, chased from the second flight while between runners heading to the turn, saved ground along the bend and advanced to come within aim nearing the top of the stretch, bumped with STRETCH RUN in upper stretch, chased to the furlong marker, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and was clear of the rest for the place. TEAGANS ATM chased from the second flight while between runners early on, exchanged bumps with AMANOFMYSTATURE nearing the turn and gave chase while outside of an inner rival along the bend, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, lacked the needed response in deep stretch but kept on and won the nod for the show on the wire. EXTRA INNINGS chased the quick early pace from the inside, gained a bit of ground along the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, could not muster a late response in deep stretch and just missed for the show. AMANOFMYSTATURE chased the fast early pace while between rivals, checked while in tight quarters approaching the turn and trailed into the bend, saved ground to to the quarter marker, was steered four wide into the stretch and passed tiring rivals in the late going. DAD BOD broke alertly and showed good early speed, set a contested pace into the turn, lost position and chased STRETCH RUN to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit to mid-stretch and faded in the final stages. NAZARE chased the solid early pace while outside of rivals, lost position while three wide nearing the quarter marker, was coaxed along five wide into the stretch and gave way. THE RIDER OF REFI NOW LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST THE RIDER OF STRETCH RUN, AND IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THE OBJECTION WOULD BE DISALLOWED. PER RULING FROM HIWU, STRETCH RUN WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Amanofmystature
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased between,checked 7/16,4wide into stretch,by tired rivals

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Stretch Run
ENTRY.COMMENT: disputed pace,led 1/4,bumped upper,kept to task deep stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Dad Bod
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,showed speed,lost position turn,faded stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Nazare
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,lost ground 3wide 1/4,5wide into stretch,gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUTISM PUZZLE broke out at the start and bothered an outside rival, showed good early speed and contested the pace into the turn, set pressured fractions while off of the rail heading to the quarter marker, shook free into the drive while on the left lead, was kept to task under steady urging to deep stretch, felt late pressure from HOMER WELLS and held off the runner-up in the final strides to prevail. HOMER WELLS broke in at the start and bothered a neighboring rival, was forwardly placed in the early running and tracked the leaders into the turn, gave chase while two wide along the bend, angled four wide into the stretch drive and ran evenly to the furlong marker, closed well in deep stretch, pressured the winner in the final stages but could not get by AUTISM PUZZLE and bested the rest. CLASSY CITY broke alertly and disputed the early pace with AUTISM PUZZLE, pressed the decent pace while three wide along the turn, came under a ride nearing the top of the lane and lost ground to AUTSIM PUZZLE into upper stretch, chased to the furlong pole, weakened in deep stretch and held safely in the end for the show. RIGHT HAND RYDER broke in at the start and was away slowly, chased the solid early pace, raced two wide along the bend and gained ground nearing the quarter marker, swung three wide for the drive and continued that steady bid to the furlong pole, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and passed a tiring rival in the final stages. M K BIRTHDAY chased the solid early pace from the inside, stalked the top pair while saving ground to the quarter marker, lost a bit of ground heading to mid-stretch and gave way in the final sixteenth. SIR GEORGE ARTHUR was prominent leaving the break and disputed the early pace, lost position heading to the turn and chased four wide along the bend, could not keep pace into upper stretch and tired. PUDDIN HEAD JONES was pinballed at the start by neighboring rivals and was away slowly, chased from the two path into upper stretch and did not factor. ROAD HOUSE broke in a step at the break, was hard to place while green in the early running and spotted the field, trailed through the turn, was steered four wide into the stretch and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Road House
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in,green/hard to place,4wide into stretch,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Autism Puzzle
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,showed speed,shook free upper,kept to task,lasted

ENTRY.NAME: Classy City
ENTRY.OWNER: Eplin Danny A Preiss Daniel and Spencer Arthur

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 83. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN broke inward after the break and veered in front of DO IT FOR DAVE, then got a good position on the inside and settled near the head of the tracking pack, started a bid near the seven-sixteenths pole but had to steady briefly in traffic, gathered up and angled to the two path for clear run, responded to vigorous handling down the stretch and got up just in time. ZOOKEEPER broke well, and went straight to the lead without much prompting, opened up on the field setting reasonable fractions to the stretch, repelled a bid by CHAMPAGNE PEGASUS at the top of the stretch then was challenged by CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN to the outside, held well but was outfinished in the shadow of the wire in a solid effort. LOVE OF THE SPORT was not asked for speed in the early going, stayed to the inside but behind the tracking pack, got a clean run to the top of the stretch, tipped out to the three path and ran on well down the stretch to gain the third spot. CHAMPAGNE PEGASUS got away well and raced close up in the two path through the first turn, tracked the pacesetter to the far turn, attempted to go after the leader under heavy pressure from the quarter pole but flattened in the stretch and was passed for a minor award. MUCHO MACHISMO came a way from the gate looking for forward position, allowed ZOOKEEPER to establish the early pace and tracked close behind, remained in contention to the far turn then was unable to keep up when the pace quickened from the quarter pole and chased the leaders to the wire. DO IT FOR DAVE broke a step slow and then had to steady as CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN took his path after the break, hurdled some rough patches in the grass passing the finish for the first time, launched a tepid rally from the half-mile marker and stayed to the inside, improved position somewhat but was not making an impression in the late stages. RULER OF ANGELS was taken in hand from the break, settled near the rear of the pack through the early stages while racing in the two to three path, was last going into the far turn but started to rally while wide, turned into the stretch five wide then finished up evenly, unable to make an impact. PORT O' CALL a little slow into stride then got hung four wide on the first turn, made some forward progress under handling down the backstretch, held position while racing wide on the far turn then ran out of steam at the top of the stretch and had little to offer from that point. COOPERKLIMT was a little keen and raced three wide into the first turn, became boxed in for the whole of the backstretch run, was unable to quicken with the pace of the race in the far turn and finished up one-paced at the tail of the field.

ENTRY.NAME: Contrary Chieftain
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, bid 7/16 then steadied, tipped out, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Do It for Dave
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, tepid inside rally, improved but no late impact

ENTRY.NAME: Love of the Sport
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled rear, kept inside, bid far turn, tipped stretch, ran on

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, bid early, ceded, tracked, chased to finish

ENTRY.OWNER: Bran Jam Stable California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC and Drenk Robert
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared field in hand, repelled foe top stretch, game, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Champagne Pegasus
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up to far turn, tracked leader 2p, bid 1/4, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Ruler of Angels
ENTRY.COMMENT: taken in hand early, trailed to far turn brief rally, needed more

ENTRY.NAME: Cooperklimt
ENTRY.OWNER: McCanna Tim McCanna Ray and Pavich Steve
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit keen first turn, boxed backstretch, outrun from 3/8

ENTRY.NAME: Port o' Call
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide both turns, mild middle move, faltered final 1/4
